-- Deripaska’s Agroholding Reaps 7.3% Bigger Sunflower Crop in 2012
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 2012-09-13T08:22:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-13/deripaska-s-agroholding-reaps-7-3-bigger-sunflower-crop-in-2012.html
Kuban Agroholding , an agricultural
company controlled by billionaire Oleg Deripaska’s Basic
Element, harvested 7.3 percent more sunflower seeds this year
than in 2011.  The crop rose to 22,542 metric tons from 21,000 tons a year
earlier, Agroholding said today in an e-mailed statement. Yields
dropped to 3.07 tons a hectare from 3.10 tons, still beating the
2.61-ton average from farmers operating in Krasnodar region,
where the company is based.  The holding operates 84,000 hectares of fields and three
silos totaling 270,000 tons in capacity, as well as seed
refineries, bakeries, a sugar plant and a stud farm in the
region, according to company data.  To contact the reporter on this story:
